news.title: Sundaram Home Finance plans to raise over Rs 6,000 crore in FY26
news.para: Sundaram Home Finance reported a 26 per cent rise in its net profit for the January-March 2025 quarter to Rs 71.57 crore from Rs 56.80 crore registered in the corresponding quarter of last financial year.

news.title: Brookfield India REIT's net operating income up 16% to Rs 488.5 crore in Q4 FY25
news.para: The company announced the distribution of Rs 319.1 crore (Rs. 5.25 per unit) to its unitholders for the March quarter, 10.5 per cent higher than the fourth quarter of the 2023-24 fiscal, according to a regulatory filing.

news.title: Activists in Vasai Virar demand SIT probe into Illegal constructions
news.para: These unauthorised structures are putting excessive pressure on the city's infrastructure, affecting water, electricity, and transport services for legitimate tax-paying residents.

news.title: Haryana cabinet approves proposal to amend policy for fixation of land rates
news.para: The Haryana Government had formulated a policy for the fixation of land market rates across all departments, boards, corporations, panchayati raj institutions, and urban local bodies.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh plans to build 60 lakh PMAY-Rural houses in FY26
news.para: The survey to assess the housing requirement started in Dec 2024 and ended in April 2025. During this period, the department received applications for over 54 lakh houses.

news.title: Housing board set to offer more than 150 plots in Siddharth Vihar, Ghaziabad
news.para: Spanning over 635 acres, the township along the Delhi-Meerut Expressway is barely a 30-minute drive from Noida City Centre and Connaught Place.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body plans crackdown on PGs lacking essential amenities
news.para: Over 1,800 PGs unauthorised, BBMP explores stricter policies to enforce civic rules, including legalising only those that meet hygiene and parking standards

news.title: Lucknow development body to begin registration of 2,502 flats in June
news.para: Under the new phase of Vishram Nagar, 1,832 EWS units (30–32 sqm), 214 LIG units (around 45 sqm), and 456 MMIG flats (approximately 55 sqm) are under construction.

news.title: Patna DM orders disposal of pending property mutation cases by May-end
news.para: Meanwhile the number of pending property mutation cases older than 75 days decreased from 80,592 to 14,108 in one year in Patna district, said DM Singh, who held a review meeting on Monday to assess the progress in land-related issues.

news.title: Nagpur civic body struggles as property tax arrears hit Rs 938 crore in 2025
news.para: While the NMC collected about Rs318 crore in property tax in the last fiscal year, the unpaid dues are almost three times of recovered amount, revealing a severe compliance and enforcement gap.

news.title: Alt DRX raises $2.7 million in new funding round
news.para: Anand Narayanan, one of the founders of Alt DRX, said the fund will be utilised for purchase of residential assets, technology, marketing and regulatory license expenses.

news.title: US-based Realty Income revises earning forecast for 2025 amid volatile market conditions
news.para: The company, however, maintained its full-year adjusted funds from operations (FFO) forecast ranging from $4.22 to $4.28 per share.

news.title: V D Savarkar's Mumbai residence could go for redevelopment: Sources
news.para: According to sources, most of the other owners have either initiated or completed agreements for redevelopment. However, no formal redevelopment proposal has been submitted, they claimed.

news.title: Odisha government suspends two tehsildars for violating plot registration norms
news.para: Earlier, the govt initiated action against 18 sub-registrars who registered 100 or more sub-plots under the development authorities, violating rules.

news.title: National Housing Bank expects RMBS firms to raise over Rs 10,000 crore in FY26
news.para: NHB Managing Director and Chief Executive Sanjay Shukla said he expects up to 10 more such transactions in the fiscal year through which lenders will raise between Rs 10,000-12,000 crore.

news.title: ED attaches Rs 2,348 crore assets in money laundering case of WTC group
news.para: The action has been taken in "a massive real estate fraud involving WTC Faridabad Infrastructure Private Limited and other entities of the WTC Group, headed by Ashish Bhalla", the Enforcement Directorate (ED) said.

news.title: Labour shortage due to heatwaves and cement price hike hit construction demand in India
news.para: Prabhudas Lilladher has put out a report after having interacted with cement dealers across regions in India to access the demand and price scenario in April 2025.

news.title: Vardhman Amrante to invest Rs 1,350 crore for realty projects in Punjab in next three years
news.para: The company plans to develop 3-4 projects, Oswal said, adding that these upcoming developments would be in residential, commercial and hospitality segments. These future projects would be certified green buildings.

news.title: SMC officials face heat over rampant illegal constructions in Surat
news.para: The issue came to light during a city coordination meeting on Saturday, where BJP MLA Arvind Rana submitted a written complaint in the presence of municipal commissioner Shalini Agarwal and other city MLAs.

news.title: Delhi: L&DO stalls conversion of leasehold properties to freehold
news.para: As per ministry's annual report for 2020-21, L&DO is responsible for the administration of about 60,526 leases of central govt land in Delhi, out of which 34,905 properties have been converted into freehold.
